</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6193E3D4FFE04815DAE88200FD26FA68" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2936B05FFFE04815DAE88200FD26FA68" blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DAE88200FEECFAB1" bold="true" box="[199,334,1333,1359]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species takes the name “gauteovan” after the Tayrona goddess as a tribute to the place from which the 
<typeStatus id="F6320EFDFFE04815DB63826DFE0CFA8C" box="[332,430,1368,1394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected. In the Tayrona culture this goddess is considered the mother of all things. The name is treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6193E3D4FFE04815DAE882AAFDA2FA23" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2936B05FFFE04815DAE882AAFDA2FA23" blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DAE882AAFEC3FA47" bold="true" box="[199,353,1439,1465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Distribution.</emphasis>
This new species is only known so far from the Tayrona National Park in the Caribbean region in 
<collectingCountry id="519EF0CFFFE04815DA9B82F6FE80FA23" box="[180,290,1475,1501]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Colombia</collectingCountry>
at sea level (
<figureCitation id="B1B2ACDAFFE04815DB9A82F6FE51FA23" box="[437,499,1475,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1123]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Map of northern South America with distribution of Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. and Mallophora kalos sp. nov. in Colombia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529459" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529459/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6193E3D4FFE04815DAE882D2FAE1F808" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2936B05FFFE04815DAE882D2FCD3F8BD" blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DAE882D2FE99F9FF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1511,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815DB6C82D2FDE4F9FF" authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[323,582,1511,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DB6C82D2FDE4F9FF" box="[323,582,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Mallophora gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815D86282D2FD0AF9FF" bold="true" box="[589,680,1511,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00CED136FFE04815D86282D2FD0AF9FF" box="[589,680,1511,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815D9D782D2FBDCF9FF" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[1016,1150,1511,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815D9D782D2FBDCF9FF" box="[1016,1150,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Mallophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the brown body color and the color pattern of the ventral setae of the hind tibia, in which there are brown setae on the basal third, whereas the apical two thirds have white setae; dorsally the setae are brown, except for a small area of white setae, increasing in size towards apex. Following the key of 
<bibRefCitation id="4D18CDAEFFE04815D89E8167FC70F992" author="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A." box="[689,978,1618,1644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="5 - 182" refId="ref4583" refString="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A. (1980) Revision del genero Mallophora Macquart por sistematica alfa y taxonomia numerica (Diptera - Asilidae). Revista Gayana Zoologia, 43 (5), 5 - 182. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 65775  / summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">Artigas &amp; Angulo (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, this species might be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815DF518166FD83F96E" authority="Artigas &amp; Angulo, 1980" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DF518166FEAEF96E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4D18CDAEFFE04815DB3C8143FD83F96E" author="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A." box="[275,545,1654,1680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="5 - 182" refId="ref4583" refString="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A. (1980) Revision del genero Mallophora Macquart por sistematica alfa y taxonomia numerica (Diptera - Asilidae). Revista Gayana Zoologia, 43 (5), 5 - 182. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 65775  / summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">Artigas &amp; Angulo, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because of the setae on the hind tibia increase in length toward the apical third, and by the white setae on the hind femur. Nonetheless, 
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815D8DA81AEFC2CF94A" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[757,910,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815D8DA81AEFC2CF94A" box="[757,910,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a black body, hyaline wings and epandrium with white setae, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815DBED818BFDFCF929" authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[450,606,1726,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DBED818BFDFCF929" box="[450,606,1726,1751]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815D84A818BFD62F926" bold="true" box="[613,704,1726,1752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00CED136FFE04815D84A818BFD62F926" box="[613,704,1726,1752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a reddish-brown body, the wings are opaque brown, and the epandria has yellow setae, same as the abdomen. More importantly, it seems from the description of 
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815DED481D7FA34F905" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[1275,1430,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DED481D7FA34F905" box="[1275,1430,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that the color pattern of the hind tibia is different, because in this species the basal has white setae, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815DF518033FEAEF8BC" authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DF518033FEAEF8BC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DB3C801CFECEF8BD" bold="true" box="[275,364,1833,1859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00CED136FFE04815DB3C801CFECEF8BD" box="[275,364,1833,1859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
only the apical two thirds ventrally are white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2936B05FFFE04815DAE88079FAE1F808" blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
Although the description is based on a single specimen, we argue that it represents a new species based on the particular color pattern of the setae on the hind legs, especially on the hind tibia. Previous evidence (
<bibRefCitation id="4D18CDAEFFE04815DF048045FE97F850" author="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A." pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="5 - 182" refId="ref4583" refString="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A. (1980) Revision del genero Mallophora Macquart por sistematica alfa y taxonomia numerica (Diptera - Asilidae). Revista Gayana Zoologia, 43 (5), 5 - 182. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 65775  / summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">Artigas &amp; Angulo, 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4D18CDAEFFE04815DB6F80A1FDB4F850" author="Kohler, A. &amp; Klein, J. &amp; Assmann, J." box="[320,534,1940,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="432 - 438" refId="ref5774" refString="Kohler, A., Klein, J. &amp; Assmann, J. (2013) Novas ocorrencias de Mallophora Macquart, 1834 (Diptera, Asilidae) no Rio Grande Do Sul: chave de identificac &quot; o e distribuic &quot; o. Brazilian Journal of Biosciences, 11 (4), 432 - 438. [http: // www. ufrgs. br / seerbio / ojs / index. php / rbb / article / view / 27]" type="journal article" year="2013">
Kohler 
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DBBA80A0FE77F850" box="[405,469,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">et al.,</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and careful examination of additional species of 
<taxonomicName id="EE89CBDCFFE04815DE6680A1FB6DF850" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[1097,1231,1940,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BFD6C4DFFE04815DE6680A1FB6DF850" box="[1097,1231,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Mallophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(S. Yepes unpubl. obs.), enable us to confirm that males of every species have a particular color pattern and chaetotaxy on the hind legs. Therefore, having a single male allows us to hypothesize that this specimen belongs to a new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
